         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Roma ¶  8th December 1881 ¶ Dear Baron ¶  ¶ I have been tossed over 300 miles west of my usual residence. Till the end of the expiring year I shall knock about this place. The trips which I planned fo...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.12.08</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Benedetto Scortechini</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by M: 'Endiandra? with large fruit'.</p>
               </note>Roma<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Qld.</p>
               </note> 8th December 1881</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Baron</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have been tossed over 300 miles west of my usual residence. Till the end of the expiring year I shall knock about this place. The trips which I planned for Wilson's Peak Fraser's Island, Bundberg<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bundaberg, Qld?</p>
               </note> have been blown to pieces by adverse winds. My Wilson's Peak trip on horseback was superseded by a trip to Warwick by rail. For the last few months I have not been master of my movements, however, after Chrismas I hope to have more time for myself.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Last Saturday week I was home, where I got your brief letter.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note> Perhaps further correspondence from you will wait there my return. In answer to your last in hand I beg to say that the large oval fruit is that of <name key="Endiandra%20Muellerii">Endiandra Muellerii</name> your fruit; in the note which I have appended<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Note not found.</p>
               </note> to said plant I mention my sending you this fruit. From the Flora I see that it is undescribed.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">In Bentham (1863-78), vol. 5, p. 302, Bentham notes of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. Muelleri</seg>: 'Fruit not seen'.</p>
               </note> It is worth describing it in your Fragmenta. It seems to be very large for its congeners. — The best specimen I could gather of <name key="Clematis%20">Clematis </name>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>No 175 has been sent to you. It was growing at the top of a stony mound isolated in the midst of a plain. It was scarse there and out of flower with no fruit. I took particular notice of the leaves which I found, every one of them, simple. As the plant withers, there is no change<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">chance.</p>
               </note> of getting better specimens till next spring. I will look out. — I plucked all the flowers of <name key="Cupania">Cupania</name> No 126, they were few, so when I went again to look for fruit, there was none. — of <name key="Myrtus">Myrtus</name> No 169 and <name key="Leptospermum">Leptospermum</name> No 154 will gather fruit, I hope, next month. I know only one little nest of <name key="Loranthus%20Bidwillii">Loranthus Bidwillii</name> growing on a pine at the mouth of Nerang Creek. If the flowers are out at my next visit to that district, the berries will be there I hope.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Since I wrote to you last I have seen the Revd. Tenison-Woods and mentioned to him your kind offer of proposing him a fellow of the Royal Society.<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">J. Tenison Woods was an unsuccessful candidate for election to the Royal Society of London in 1883, with M as his principal sponsor, and again in 1884 and then each year from 1886 to 1888.</p>
               </note> He would be glad of the honor. He told me he was going to write to you on the subject. I expect he has done it already.<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note> You may kindly take steps for his proposal. His scientific labours deserve some honorable recognition. Yesterday he started for Bathurst N. S. Wales. Between scientific and ecclesiastic work he has been labouring hard in the past few months.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am terribly disappointed with this place in a botanical point of view. Few desert plants make their appearance here. There only one <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name>, which I have not identified as yet, the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Acacia</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">pendula</hi>
               </seg>, and another brigalow; sometimes I meet Acacia Farnesiana very stunted in growth. Two heremophilas,<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Eremophilas?</p>
               </note> Mitchelli and longifolia, gejera parviflora,<note xml:id="ftn11" type="footnote" n="11">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Geijera parviflora</seg>?</p>
               </note> and <name key="Apophyllum%20anomalum">Apophyllum anomalum</name> constitute mostly the whole scrub and forest vegetation. <name key="Boerhavia%20diffusa">Boerhavia diffusa</name>, <name key="Tribulus%20terrestris">Tribulus terrestris</name>, and several <name key="Chenopodiaceae">Chenopodiaceae</name> monopolize the small growth. To-morrow I will be out exploring, with little success, I expect. In a hundred miles of this country there are not many more varieties than in one single acre.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I do not know whether you may wish to have some particular observation made on some plants, which may be growing about here; if so let me know it at once. You may address your letter to Roma, from where I shall start towards the end of the month, so an early letter from you will find me here, any other will get me at the Logan.<note xml:id="ftn12" type="footnote" n="12">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Logan River, Qld.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With my best regards I remain</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your humble Servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B Scortechini</p>
